Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 120 MONTHS, concurrent with 06CF5521, with credit for 176 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 60 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 60 MONTHS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment or counseling;
2) No contact with any known gang members;
3) Defendant is prohibited from being present where controlled substances are used, sold, or packaged for sale;
4) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
5) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharges;
6) No firearms may be present in the defendant's residence;

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
